Forty-two states and Washington, D.C., have smoking restrictions in hospitals (an increase of one state [i.e., Tennessee] since the 1995 report); 40 states and Washington, D.C., on selected forms of public transportation; 29 states and Washington, D.C., in grocery stores; and 23 states in enclosed arenas.
